		href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Mukta:wght@200;300;400;500;600;700;800&family=Secular+One&display=swap"
		rel="stylesheet">

	<style>
		* {
			box-sizing: border-box;
		}

		html,
		body {
			margin: 0;
			padding: 0;
			width: 100%;
			height: 100%;
			overflow: hidden;
			/* background-color: #7eb6d9; */
			font-family: 'Mukta', sans-serif;
			display: flex;
			align-items: center;
			justify-content: center;
		}

		.container {
			max-height: 100vh;
			align-items: center;
		}

		.left-side {
			position: absolute;
			z-index: 1;
			left: 20%;
			bottom: 10%;
		}

		.right-side {
			position: absolute;
			z-index: 1;
			right: 20%;
			bottom: 10%;
		}

		#back,
		.ten,
		#next {
			justify-self: center;
			align-self: center;
			font-family: 'Secular One', sans-serif;
		}

		#back {
			position: absolute;
			z-index: 1;
			left: 5%;
			bottom: 50px;
			text-align: left;
		}

		.pres {
			position: absolute;
			top: 0;
			left: 0;
			z-index: 0;
		}

		#next {
			position: absolute;
			z-index: 1;
			right: 5%;
			bottom: 50px;
			text-align: right;
		}

		p {
			margin: 10px;
			padding: 20px;
			font-size: 16px;
			background-color: #7EB6D9;
			/* border: 2px solid #ADE0FF; */
			max-width: 400px;
			width: 25%;
			box-shadow: -1px 1px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.507);
		}

		button {
			display: block;
			width: 100px;
			height: 40px;
			background-color: #ADE0FF;
			border: none;
			box-shadow: none;
			transition: box-shadow 0.3s linear;
			margin: 0.5em;
			cursor: pointer;
			font-size: 1.2em;
		}

		button:hover {
			box-shadow: 0px 0px 0px 5px #ADE0FF;
		}

		#next:active,
		#back:active {
			box-shadow: 0px 0px 0px 5px #5a829b;
			background-color: #5a829b;
		}

		canvas {
			border-radius: 1em;
			width: 100%;
			height: 800px;
		}

		@media (max-width: 1300px) {
			p {
				max-width: 280px;
				width: 40%;
				margin: 0;
			}

			.left-side {
				left: 20%;
			}

			.right-side {
				right: 20%;
			}
		}

		@media (max-width: 900px) {
			.left-side {
				left: 30px;
				bottom: 150px;
			}

			.right-side {
				right: 30px;
				bottom: 150px;
			}
		}
	</style>

</head>

<body>
	<noscript>Please enable JavaScript in your web browser to view this page.</noscript>
	<div class='container'>
		<!-- titleScene -->
		<p class='left-side' data-key='1'>
			Welcome to Harmonic Presence! In this interactive presentation, you will learn about the existence of
			harmonics in sound through audio and visual examples.
		</p>
		<p class='right-side' data-key='1'>
			By the end of this presentation, you will be able to describe harmonics in math, physics, and musical terms,
			and you will know how they contribute to beautiful sounds. Click Next to dive in.
		</p>

		<!-- basics -->
		<p class='left-side' style='display: none' data-key='2'>
			We can identify a sound by its pitch, or <b>frequency</b>. Most of the time, however, there are multiple sound
			waves, with varying frequencies, that make up a sound. What we are really identifying is called the
			<b>fundamental frequency</b>.
		</p>
		<p class='right-side' style='display: none' data-key='2'>
			The <b>fundamental frequency</b> is the loudest of all of the frequencies, which is why we hear it the most.
			All of the other quieter frequencies are called Harmonics.
		</p>

		<!-- harmonic sound example -->
		<p class='left-side' style='display: none' data-key='3'>
			A sound without harmonics is a single sound wave, like a sine wave.
			The robot represents a sine wave, since it is a synthetically created sound. Click on the robot to hear a sound
			without harmonics.
		</p>
		<p class='right-side' style='display: none' data-key='3'>
			The piano represents a note being played on a piano. Click on the piano to hear the piano note. The difference in
			tone is because of the presence of harmonics!
		</p>

		<!-- frequencyBasics -->
		<p class='left-side' style='display: none' data-key='4'>
			Both notes you heard in the previous example have a frequency of 440 Hertz.
		</p>
		<p class='right-side' style='display: none' data-key='4'>
			Let's go over what this means exactly.
		</p>

		<!-- frequencyBasics -->
		<p class='left-side' style='display: none' data-key='5'>
			Frequency represents the pitch of a sound wave, which corresponds to the number
			of vibrations per second. It is measured in Hertz.
		</p>
		<p class='right-side' style='display: none' data-key='5'>
			When we say that a note is 440 Hertz, that means that the sound wave vibrates 440 times
			per second.
		</p>

		<div class='pres' id="pixi-content">
			<canvas id="pixi-canvas" />
		</div>
		<button id='next'>Next</button>
	</div>
</body>

</html>